# Main

## Rendell E. de Kort {#title}

### Development Economist

100% Aruban economist with 8 years Central Bank of Aruba experience and international expertise in monetary policy and Small Island Developing States economic resilience.

## Professional Experience {data-icon="suitcase"}

### Research Economist

Central Bank of Aruba

Oranjestad, Aruba

2010 - 2018

::: concise
-   **Monetary Policy Support**: Spearheaded development and maintenance of macroeconomic forecasting models for monetary policy decisions
-   **Financial System Analysis**: Conducted comprehensive analysis of Aruba's financial sector and banking system stability
-   **Institutional Leadership**: Served as Secretary to Monetary Policy Committee and Coordination Committee of public sector
-   **Economic Communication**: Formulated and communicated official economic narratives and policy positions
:::

### Senior Economic Advisor 

To the Minister of Finance, Economic Affairs and Agriculture, Government of Aruba

Oranjestad, Aruba

2025 - Present

::: concise
-   **Policy Analysis**: High-level economic analysis for government leadership on fiscal and monetary matters
-   **Parliamentary Engagement**: Economic analysis presented and defended at parliamentary level
-   **Crisis Preparedness**: Scenario planning for external economic shocks including potential trade disruptions
:::

### Economist Consultant

The World Bank

Remote (Washington, DC office)

2020 - Present

::: concise
-   **Central Bank Advisory**: Disaster Risk Financing assessments for Caribbean central banks and governments
-   **Financial System Resilience**: Structuring catastrophe deferred drawdown options (CAT-DDO) for sovereign risk management
-   **Regional Expertise**: Post-disaster needs assessments across Caribbean SIDS
-   **International Standards**: Application of global best practices to small island financial systems
:::

